29:39.837 --> 29:41.820
It was always a good place for working.

29:43.142 --> 29:57.967
So was Paris, and so were Key West Florida in the cool months, the ranch near Cook City, Montana, Kansas City, Chicago, Toronto, and Havana, Cuba.

29:57.987 --> 30:03.516
Some other places were not so good, but maybe we were not so good when we were in them.

30:10.398 --> 30:14.762
There was a long white beach with coconut palms behind it.

30:15.743 --> 30:26.553
The reef lay across the entrance of the harbor and the heavy east wind made the sea break on it so that the entrance was easy to see once you had opened it up.

30:27.594 --> 30:33.139
There was no one on the beach and the sand was so white that it hurt your eyes to look at it.

30:34.781 --> 30:37.323
The man on the flying bridge studied the shore.

30:38.084 --> 30:39.105
There were no shack

30:39.929 --> 30:45.977
where the shacks should have been, and there were no boats anchored in the lagoon that he could see.

30:47.699 --> 30:50.403
You've been in here before, he said to his mate.

30:50.964 --> 30:51.264
Yes.

30:52.466 --> 30:53.848
Weren't the shacks over there?

30:53.868 --> 30:57.633
They were over there, and it shows a village on a chart.

30:58.794 --> 31:02.359
They sure as hell aren't there now, the man said.

31:03.541 --> 31:05.844
Can you make out any boats up in the mangroves?

31:06.845 --> 31:08.367
There's nothing that I can see.

31:08.971 --> 31:11.554
I'm going to take her in and anchor, the man said.

31:12.375 --> 31:13.336
I know this cut.

31:13.797 --> 31:15.699
It's about eight times as deep as it looks.

31:17.121 --> 31:22.507
He looked down into the green water and saw the size of the shadow of his ship on the bottom.

31:24.009 --> 31:28.234
There's good holding ground east from where the village used to be, his mate said.

31:29.116 --> 31:29.396
I know.

31:30.077 --> 31:32.239
Break out the starboard anchor and stand by.

31:32.259 --> 31:33.941
I'm going to lay off there.

31:34.582 --> 31:37.746
With this wind blowing day and night, there will be no insects.

31:38.536 --> 31:38.998
No, sir.

31:40.222 --> 31:42.269
They anchored in the boat.

31:42.289 --> 31:47.888
She was not big enough to be called a ship except in the mind of the man who was her master.

